<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,439,464]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Distribution.</emphasis>
Primarily a west coast species, from Washington to southern California, with a few records from high elevation localities in Wyoming, Utah and Colorado.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,512,536]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species seems to get transported around in lumber, as there is a record from Alaska emerging from pine 
<number box="[275,291,548,572]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="2.0">2</number>
<date box="[291,323,548,572]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
x 
<number box="[307,323,548,572]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="2.0">2</number>
</date>
’s, and a record from New York emerging from cedar wood, however, there is no evidence that suggests that this species is established in these areas.
</paragraph>
